Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1%unit} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Pop the veg chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and starting to char, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the @water{300%milliliter} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the everything cooks, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams} with half the coriander. Season with @salt and @pepper, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the kidney beans, garlic and @Caribbean style jerk{2%sachets}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%min}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{150%milliliter} for the sauce to the pan.

Bring the stew to the boil, then lower the heat medium. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{6-8%mins}.

When there are about 5 mins left of veg roasting time, drizzle over the @honey{15%grams} and return to the oven for the remaining time.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Once the stew is reduced, stir through the roasted veg. Season with @salt and @pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if the stew is a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining coriander, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the roasted vegetable stew and a dollop of coriander yoghurt.

Enjoy!